<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>About | GunitaPH</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/images/gunita-logo.png" type="image/png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/main.css">
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="container about-container">
    
        <a href="/" class="back-btn">← Back</a>

        <div class="about-page">

            <div class="logo">
            <h1 class="name"><span>G</span>UNITA</h1>
            </div>

            <h1 class="about-title">About GunitaPH</h1>

            <div class="about-section">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                GunitaPH is a local travel forum designed for people who want to explore
                destinations in the Philippines through shared experiences, tips, and
                discussions from fellow travelers.
            </p>
            <p>
                Information about traveling within the Philippines is widely available online,
                but much of it is scattered across different websites, blogs, and social media
                platforms. Because of this, travelers may find it difficult to locate organized
                and reliable information in one place. GunitaPH was developed to address this
                gap by providing a community-driven platform where users can share experiences,
                ask questions, and exchange travel advice.
            </p>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section">
            <h2>What the Platform Offers</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Create and share travel posts</li>
                <li>Upload images from trips</li>
                <li>Comment and reply to discussions</li>
                <li>Like or dislike posts</li>
                <li>Edit profiles and posts</li>
                <li>Filter content based on destination and travel style</li>
            </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section">
            <h2>Technologies and NPM Packages Used</h2>
            <p>
                The application is built using the following technologies and Node.js packages:
            </p>

            <h3>Core Backend</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Express.js</strong> – Handles routing, server logic, and HTTP requests</li>
                <li><strong>Mongoose</strong> – Connects Node.js to MongoDB and manages schemas and models</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Authentication and Security</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>express-session</strong> – Handles user sessions and login persistence</li>
                <li><strong>bcrypt</strong> – Encrypts user passwords securely through hashing</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Templating / Frontend Rendering</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>express-handlebars</strong> – Renders dynamic <code>.hbs</code> pages</li>
                <li><strong>hbs</strong> – Included as a Handlebars-related dependency in the project</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>File Uploads</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Multer</strong> – Handles image uploads for posts and profile pictures</li>
            </ul>

            <p>
                These technologies work together to create a full-stack web application with
                dynamic content, user authentication, and database integration.
            </p>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section">
            <h2>Project Note</h2>
            <p>
                GunitaPH was developed as a CCAPDEV project focused on building an interactive,
                community-driven platform for sharing travel experiences in the Philippines.
            </p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>